cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the use of D2D communications to improve data uploading in LTE-A systems. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of channel quality differences to develop D2D-based solutions. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper mentions uploading data to the Cloud. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes enhanced D2D-based solutions that involve cooperative sharing of resources. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as there is no explicit mention of security or cryptography in the abstract.
